{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Reverse Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Reverse Filter</h1>

<p>Reverses the order of elements in an array.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ array | reverse }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% assign fruits = "apple,banana,cherry" | split: "," %}
{{ fruits | reverse | join: ", " }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> cherry, banana, apple</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% assign nums = "1,2,3,4,5" | split: "," %}
{{ nums | reverse | join: " " }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 5 4 3 2 1</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>Returns a new array; the original is not modified. The filter operates on any array value.</p>

